2026-04-03 | Print Anti-Diagonals of Matrix

	Question
Return all elements grouped by anti-diagonals.

	Approach
1.	Total diagonals = 2*n - 1  
2.	For each diagonal d:
		i + j = d  

3.	Iterate:
		i from 0 to n-1  
		j = d - i  

4.	Ensure:
		j is within bounds  

5.	Collect elements for each diagonal  

	Time Complexity
	O(n²)

	Space Complexity
	O(n²)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> antiDiagonal(vector<vector<int>>& mat) {

        int n = mat.size();
        vector<vector<int>> ans;

        for(int d = 0; d < 2*n - 1; d++){

            vector<int> temp;

            for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
                int j = d - i;

                if(j >= 0 && j < n){
                    temp.push_back(mat[i][j]);
                }
            }

            ans.push_back(temp);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
All elements on same anti-diagonal satisfy:
		i + j = constant  

By iterating over all possible sums (0 → 2n-2),
we can extract all diagonals efficiently.
